[
    {
        "text": "Do you want to see my new favourite shape?",
        "start": 0.0,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "Yeah of course you do! It's this one here,",
        "start": 2.24,
        "duration": 2.63
    },
    {
        "text": "it's called the largest small hexagon.",
        "start": 5.44,
        "duration": 3.92
    },
    {
        "text": "And I just love it because I love its",
        "start": 9.36,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "name, the largest small hexagon. So let's",
        "start": 10.8,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "break down what the name means; so it's a",
        "start": 13.44,
        "duration": 2.079
    },
    {
        "text": "hexagon, which is a six sided shape. Small",
        "start": 15.519,
        "duration": 3.041
    },
    {
        "text": "means that all the diagonals, like corner",
        "start": 18.56,
        "duration": 2.799
    },
    {
        "text": "to corner, they're all less than and",
        "start": 21.359,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "equal to 1, that's what small means. And",
        "start": 23.279,
        "duration": 2.881
    },
    {
        "text": "then largest small hexagon means it has",
        "start": 26.16,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "the largest area with that rule. If all",
        "start": 28.64,
        "duration": 2.879
    },
    {
        "text": "the diagonals are less than or equal to",
        "start": 31.519,
        "duration": 2.641
    },
    {
        "text": "1 the idea is it could fit",
        "start": 34.16,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "in a",
        "start": 36.64,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "1x1 box like that.",
        "start": 38.0,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "In fact you could roll it around inside",
        "start": 40.8,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "that box and it would fit nicely in",
        "start": 42.64,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "there.",
        "start": 45.2,
        "duration": 0.85
    },
    {
        "text": "What's surprising is it's not the",
        "start": 47.36,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "regular hexagon, because that's what my",
        "start": 49.68,
        "duration": 1.44
    },
    {
        "text": "guess would have been. Okay what is the",
        "start": 51.12,
        "duration": 2.079
    },
    {
        "text": "largest area if you had all the",
        "start": 53.199,
        "duration": 2.801
    },
    {
        "text": "diagonals fitting inside a 1x1",
        "start": 56.0,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "box? And I would have guessed regular",
        "start": 57.84,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "hexagon.",
        "start": 60.0,
        "duration": 0.79
    },
    {
        "text": "But it's not. So it's this thing so this",
        "start": 62.32,
        "duration": 2.159
    },
    {
        "text": "is not a regular hexagon, it's irregular,",
        "start": 64.479,
        "duration": 2.481
    },
    {
        "text": "it has a larger area than the regular",
        "start": 66.96,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "hexagon by about 4% and this",
        "start": 69.68,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "was discovered in the 1970s by Ron",
        "start": 72.64,
        "duration": 2.799
    },
    {
        "text": "Graham. So let me show you a little bit",
        "start": 75.439,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "more about this. So I was surprised that",
        "start": 77.439,
        "duration": 2.481
    },
    {
        "text": "it wasn't a regular hexagon, and if we",
        "start": 79.92,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "did shapes with less sides it",
        "start": 81.92,
        "duration": 2.559
    },
    {
        "text": "actually is the regular shape.",
        "start": 84.479,
        "duration": 2.081
    },
    {
        "text": "So for a triangle",
        "start": 86.56,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "the largest small triangle",
        "start": 87.92,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "is",
        "start": 89.92,
        "duration": 0.96
    },
    {
        "text": "the regular equilateral triangle; these",
        "start": 90.88,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "have a side length 1",
        "start": 93.68,
        "duration": 2.079
    },
    {
        "text": "and that would be your answer.",
        "start": 95.759,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "For a quadrilateral",
        "start": 98.079,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "it is the square, the square has",
        "start": 100.479,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "diagonals of 1. So it's not side length",
        "start": 102.479,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "1, it's diagonals of length 1, that is",
        "start": 105.119,
        "duration": 2.721
    },
    {
        "text": "your largest small quadrilateral.",
        "start": 107.84,
        "duration": 3.919
    },
    {
        "text": "Although there's more than one answer",
        "start": 111.759,
        "duration": 2.161
    },
    {
        "text": "for the quadrilateral, because it could",
        "start": 113.92,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "be",
        "start": 115.92,
        "duration": 0.799
    },
    {
        "text": "any quadrilateral which has two",
        "start": 116.719,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "diagonals that are at right angles to",
        "start": 119.119,
        "duration": 2.481
    },
    {
        "text": "each other that have length 1; this has",
        "start": 121.6,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "length 1 and this has length 1 like",
        "start": 123.92,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "that. If I put them like that that would",
        "start": 125.84,
        "duration": 2.399
    },
    {
        "text": "be a square but I could have a",
        "start": 128.239,
        "duration": 1.921
    },
    {
        "text": "quadrilateral of any sort of kite shape",
        "start": 130.16,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "like this and those would all have the",
        "start": 132.72,
        "duration": 1.519
    },
    {
        "text": "same answer, they all have the same area",
        "start": 134.239,
        "duration": 1.601
    },
    {
        "text": "so they all count as the largest small",
        "start": 135.84,
        "duration": 2.479
    },
    {
        "text": "quadrilateral. If you're looking at the",
        "start": 138.319,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "pentagon it's the regular pentagon. So",
        "start": 140.319,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "here is the regular pentagon and then",
        "start": 142.879,
        "duration": 1.921
    },
    {
        "text": "your diagonals have length 1 and that",
        "start": 144.8,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "is the largest small",
        "start": 147.44,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "pentagon. So therefore you think, ah the",
        "start": 149.04,
        "duration": 3.04
    },
    {
        "text": "largest small hexagon",
        "start": 152.08,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "would be the regular hexagon,",
        "start": 154.0,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "here it is, but it turns out",
        "start": 156.4,
        "duration": 2.479
    },
    {
        "text": "it's not.",
        "start": 158.879,
        "duration": 2.161
    },
    {
        "text": "So to solve this what Ron Graham did is",
        "start": 161.04,
        "duration": 2.479
    },
    {
        "text": "he used some graph theory, which is a",
        "start": 163.519,
        "duration": 2.481
    },
    {
        "text": "little bit surprising. Graph theory is",
        "start": 166.0,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "the maths of points and networks, so dots",
        "start": 168.0,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "and lines; and he knew that some of these",
        "start": 170.72,
        "duration": 2.159
    },
    {
        "text": "diagonals had to have length 1. And he",
        "start": 172.879,
        "duration": 2.561
    },
    {
        "text": "just kind of looked at all the",
        "start": 175.44,
        "duration": 1.04
    },
    {
        "text": "possibilities and he drew them as graphs,",
        "start": 176.48,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
        "text": "he knew that some of these possibilities",
        "start": 178.64,
        "duration": 2.08
    },
    {
        "text": "were definitely not going to be the",
        "start": 180.72,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "largest area, so he could get rid of",
        "start": 182.4,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "those. And he had about",
        "start": 184.08,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
